 calculate the area of this sector, the length of the arc, and the chord le=
ngth is fundamental in various fields, from mathematics to engineering.</p>=
<h3 class=3D"text-default mb-2 font-semibold mt-4 text-xl">Key Formulas:</h=
3><ul class=3D"text-default list-disc pl-5 space-y-2"><li><strong>Sector Ar=
ea:</strong> The area of a sector is proportional to the central angle. <sp=
an>$$ Area =3D \frac{\theta}{360} \times \pi r^2 $$</span> (for degrees) or=
 <span>$$ Area =3D \frac{\theta}{2\pi} \times \pi r^2 =3D \frac{1}{2} r^2 \=
theta $$</span> (for radians), where \( \theta \) is the central angle and =
\( r \) is the radius.</li><li><strong>Arc Length:</strong> The arc length =
is the distance along the arc of the sector. <span>$$ Arc Length =3D \frac{=
\theta}{360} \times 2 \pi r $$</span> (for degrees) or <span>$$ Arc Length =
=3D r \theta $$</span> (for radians).</li><li><strong>Chord Length:</strong=
> The chord length is the straight line distance between the two endpoints =
of the arc. <span>$$ Chord Length =3D 2r \sin(\frac{\theta}{2}) $$</span> (=
where \( \theta \) is in degrees, used in sine function as degrees).</li></=
ul><h3 class=3D"text-default mb-2 font-semibold mt-4 text-xl">Use Cases:</h=
3><p class=3D"text-default">These calculations are useful in various applic=
